I haven’t done this personally but have a friend who does coaching/consulting and has always offered some form of followup. Here’s an example from her website—it might be helpful in that it doesn’t give a strict yes/no list, but sets it up in the form of questions clients may have after you wrap up the 5-day session.
&gt; *What does the week of email support include?*
&gt; 
&gt; Every coaching client gets seven days of email support after our live session.
&gt; 
&gt; Do you have a follow up question about your post-session packet? Did you take my advice about getting new clients and now you have a new client and you’re not sure what to do? Did our work shake loose some new ideas you want feedback on?
&gt; 
&gt; Great! My inbox is open to you for a week.
&gt; 
&gt; Most of my post-session support comes in the form of Loom video replies; it’s faster and soooo much more personal!
(from <https://yesandyes.org/1-on-1-coaching|yesandyes.org’s 1-on-1 coaching page>)
